  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, monsoon mornings make me happy, they feel fresh and full of possibility. How was your baking experiment with banana bread?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The banana bread was so-so. Recipe said 45 mins, but I think I overbaked it. My kitchen smells nice though. I need more practice."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Overbaking happens, I get that. The nice smell is a win! What will you try next?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe try a cake recipe next. I like how it turned out. Or maybe chapati, but that’s not English. Hmm."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Cake sounds fun, you did great with the bread. Chapati is totally fine to talk about, no rules here. What kind of cake?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe a chocolate cake? I have a recipe from my aunt. But I’m scared to try it. What if I fail again?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Scared is normal, even with a good recipe. Go for it, what’s the next step?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Next step is to buy the ingredients. I need chocolate, eggs, sugar... Maybe I can ask my sister to come help. She’s better at cooking than me."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Getting ingredients is a solid start. Having help makes it even better, what chocolate do you need?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Dark chocolate, maybe. My aunt’s recipe says 70% cocoa. I don’t know what that means exactly. Should I get the really bitter kind? Or the sweet one? I’m confused."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"70% cocoa is the sweet spot, rich but not too bitter. Go with that, and take your time. How do you feel about starting?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I feel okay. A bit nervous, but okay. Let’s do it. Maybe I’ll call her “70% chocolate” even if it’s not. Sounds good in Marathi, “70 pratiśat kheer chocolate\". Maza hojayach!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Calling it 70% sounds fun, and your Marathi twist adds a sweet touch. Take your time, and have fun with it, tell me how it goes?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Will do. Thanks. Need to go prep for a study session now. Talk later."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Study session first, got it. Take your time, and share how the cake turns out. All the best!\""
    }
  ],
